      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The quantities of interest must be directly linked to the clinical decision endpoint (hemolysis index) with documented traceability at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index is identified as the primary QoI and is computed from shear stress history. Traceability to the clinical endpoint is partially documented but linkage to patient-level outcomes is not established."
